title: High school football: Westmont ends slide with win against Seneca
text:
High school football: Westmont ends slide with win against Seneca Published: Saturday, Oct. 3, 2015 12:18 a.m. CDT By SUBURBAN LIFE MEDIA 
WESTMONT â€“ Westmont High School celebrated its homecoming on Oct. 2, but that's not the only reason it needed a win. 
The Sentinels snapped a four-game losing streak and kept their playoff hopes alive with a 34-7 win against Seneca. 
It was the highest point total for the Sentinels (2-4 overall, 1-3 Interstate Eight Small) since a Week 1 win against Chicago Christian. 
Westmont travels to Reed-Custer on Oct. 9 in the conference finale for both teams.
